<h1>Metronome, Pok&eacute;mon attack </h1>
<p class="subtitle">From <a href="http://www.jonnydigital.com/">Jonathan's Reference Pages</a></p>
<hr><!-- ======================================================== -->


<p>The Metronome is one of the most unusual <a title="attacks"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=attacks&lastnode_id=95452">attacks</a> 
from the <a title="popular"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=popular&lastnode_id=95452">popular</a> 
<a title="animé"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=anim%E9&lastnode_id=95452">animé</a>/<a 
title="cartoon"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=cartoon&lastnode_id=95452">cartoon</a> 
<a title="series"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=series&lastnode_id=95452">series</a> 
and <a title="video game"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=video%20game&lastnode_id=95452">video 
game</a>, <a title="Pokémon"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Pok%E9mon&lastnode_id=95452">Pokémon</a>, 
having a totally random effect each time it is used.
</p>

<p>
In the <a title="Pokémon"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Pok%E9mon&lastnode_id=95452">Pokémon</a> 
Red, Blue and Yellow <a title="game"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=game&lastnode_id=95452">game</a>s, 
the Metronome performs one <a title="TM"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=TM&lastnode_id=95452">TM</a>
attack at random. In <a title="Pokémon"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Pok%E9mon&lastnode_id=95452">Pokémon</a> 
Gold, Silver and Crystal, Metronome performs <i>any</i> attack at
random, not just <a title="TM"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=TM&lastnode_id=95452">TM</a>s.
</p>

<p>
<a title="Clefairy"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Clefairy&lastnode_id=95452">Clefairy</a> 
learns metronome naturally at Level 31 and <a title="Mew"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Mew&lastnode_id=95452">Mew</a> 
learns it at Level 30. Metronome can be taught to the following <a
title="Pokémon"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Pok%E9mon&lastnode_id=95452">Pokémon</a> 
using <a title="TM"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=TM&lastnode_id=95452">TM</a>35 
(found on <a title="Cinnibar Island"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Cinnibar%20Island&lastnode_id=95452">Cinnibar 
Island</a>): Clefairy, Clefable, Poliwhirl, Abra, Kadabra, <a
title="Alakazam"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Alakazam&lastnode_id=95452">Alakazam</a>, 
Geodude, Graveller, Golem, Gengar, Drowzee, Hypno, Chansey, Mr.Mime,
Jynx, Electabuzz, Magmar, Snorlax, Mewtwo, Mew and all fighting type <a
title="Pokémon"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Pok%E9mon&lastnode_id=95452">Pokémon</a>.
</p>

<p>
As seen in a number of <a title="episodes"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=episodes&lastnode_id=95452">episodes</a> 
of the <a title="animé"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=anim%E9&lastnode_id=95452">animé</a>/<a 
title="cartoon"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=cartoon&lastnode_id=95452">cartoon</a> 
series, "just about anything can happen" when the Metronome is
performed. In this case, the usage of the Metronome is not specifically
limited to a specific named attack - in one episode, <a title="Togepi"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Togepi&lastnode_id=95452">Togepi</a> 
manages a huge explosion of some kind by way of this attack, although
which attack this actually was isn't entirely clear.
</p>

<p>
<a title="Pokémon"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Pok%E9mon&lastnode_id=95452">Pokémon</a> 
seen in the <a title="series"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=series&lastnode_id=95452">series</a> 
to use the Metronome include <a title="Togepi"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Togepi&lastnode_id=95452">Togepi</a>, 
<a title="Clefairy"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Clefairy&lastnode_id=95452">Clefairy</a> 
and <a title="Drowzee"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Drowzee&lastnode_id=95452">Drowzee</a>.</p>




